    "Opportunities for Individualized Emotional SupportGrounded in participants' custimization practices and design ideas, this section discusses opportunities for designing more effective and empathetic chatbots to address individualized emotional needs, as well as with rising challenges.",
    "Building emotional connections through multiple channels.Our findings showed that participants desired an emotional connection with the chatbot.",
    "As presented in Section 5.3.1, participants often began confiding during the customization stage, describing their struggles, interpersonal conflicts, and work challenges.",
    "Interestingly, participants sometimes express their mood through the choice of avatars for themselves (e.g., using (sad face) to express unhappiness), and for the chatbot as if it could recognize their unhappiness and empathize with them by showing an angry face (e.g., using), despite knowing that it could not.",
    "By shaping such emotional dynamics, participants made the chatbot \"visually empathetic,\" creating an impression that their feelings could be recognized and understood throughout the conversations."
  ],
